# Forge in Cursor

Universal Forge behavior (**blocking prompts**, **stage-local questioning**, **interactive human input**) is defined once in **`skills/using-forge/SKILL.md`** for **every** supported IDE — not Cursor-only. This file adds **Cursor-specific** tool aliases and reminders.

Forge skills load from **`~/.cursor/plugins/local/forge/skills/`** after **`scripts/install.sh --platform cursor`**. On every session start, read **`~/.cursor/plugins/local/forge/skills/using-forge/SKILL.md`**. Key commands include **`/forge`**, **`/workspace`**, **`/intake`**, **`/qa`**, **`/qa-write`**, **`/qa-run`** — full list in plugin **`commands/`**.

## `AskUserQuestion` → `AskQuestion` (Cursor alias)

Forge **`SKILL.md`** files name the blocking multiple-choice tool **`AskUserQuestion`** (canonical for Claude Code, `allowed-tools` policy, CI). **In Cursor sessions, use `AskQuestion`** with the same title, text, and options — same semantics as **`using-forge`** **Blocking interactive prompts**.

If `AskQuestion` is not available or a call fails, present the same choices as a **numbered list** in the assistant message, **stop**, and wait for the user. Do not skip skill gates that depend on a human answer.

**Do not** mass-rename `AskUserQuestion` in `SKILL.md` files; keep skills canonical for other hosts and CI.

## Interactive human input (project standard — all hosts)

Any **doubt, question, confirmation, or choice** that needs a human answer — including **task-id**, **next step**, **waiver**, **priority** — must use a **blocking interactive prompt** or **numbered list + stop**, not prose-only *“reply if…”* walls. In Cursor that is usually **`AskQuestion`**. Full norm: **`using-forge`** → **Interactive human input** (applies to Gemini CLI, JetBrains, Codex, etc., with host mapping in that skill).

**Invalid:** A **“What to do next”** markdown section that ends with *“reply with task-id / confirm you started …”* **without** **`AskQuestion`** or **numbered options in the same message** — that fails **interactive human input**. Always append **`AskQuestion`** or **numbered choices** for the **first** real fork.

## Chat-visible questioning & multi-question elicitation

**Project standard (all skills):** **`skills/using-forge/SKILL.md`** → **Multi-question elicitation** — **transcript-first**, **one primary topic per message** when multiple answers are needed, **blocking** **`AskQuestion`** / **numbered options + stop** for discrete forks, **reconcile** after each reply. Applies to intake, council, planning, QA, env choices — **not** only one skill.

**Examples:** **`intake-interrogate` Q9** — **verbatim** design blockquote in thread. **`qa-prd-analysis` Step 0.5** — same pattern for coverage **Q1–Q8**. **Forbidden:** full questionnaire dump + unrelated meta-prompt in one turn; brain-only “confirmed” without thread.

**Forbidden bundle:** **One** **`AskQuestion`** plus a prose wall demanding **other** needle-moving answers **and** unrelated roadmap / waiver text **in the same message** — use **sequential turns** (**`using-forge`** item **6**; **`docs/forge-one-step-horizon.md`** **No bundled unrelated decisions**).

**Question-forward / no trailing nag / no downstream essays:** **`docs/forge-one-step-horizon.md`** **Question-forward elicitation** and **No defensive downstream-gate narration (repo-wide)**; **`using-forge`** items **7–8**. Do **not** paste *why semantic machine eval (or any later gate) isn’t ready yet* between normal Q1→Q2-style turns — that copy is for **reference** or **skip-ahead refusal** only.

**No dual prompts:** Do **not** show **`AskQuestion`** / **Questions** for one fork (e.g. approve **task-id** / **prd-locked**) **and** put a **different** long markdown question (e.g. **Q1** test-type checklist) in the **same** assistant message — **one primary question per turn** (**forge-one-step-horizon** **No bundled unrelated decisions**).

**No chat–widget duplicate (same question):** Put the **long** list / prompt in **chat** **once**; the **Questions** UI = **short** title + **options** — **not** the full same block again (**forge-one-step-horizon** **Chat vs `AskQuestion` / Questions widget**).

**In Cursor you MUST:** output chat-visible text so the transcript shows what was asked; then **`AskQuestion`** when choices are discrete.

**Why this breaks more often in Cursor:** no per-message reinjection hook — only **session-start** loads **`using-forge`**.

**If the user says questions never appeared:** re-run the phase per **`using-forge`** **Multi-question elicitation** and the active skill’s HARD-GATE; do not write only to brain.

## Automation ≠ assumption

Forge **automates artifacts and pipelines** — not **decisions**. At every **needle-moving** step (scope, design authority, prioritization, waivers), use **`AskQuestion`** (or numbered choices) and **wait**. Do **not** infer “confirmed” answers from docs alone; see **`using-forge`**.

**Stage-local questioning — respect process order:** Ask only what unblocks the **current** Forge stage (or the **next** prerequisite in dependency order). **Do not** open with a **blocking prompt** about **later** phases when upstream prerequisites are still missing. Fix the **first** gap first. **Do not** narrate the full downstream roadmap in chat **before** the user is there — **one-step horizon** unless they asked “what’s after?” Full norm: **`using-forge`** → **Stage-local questioning** + **horizon narration**; **`docs/forge-one-step-horizon.md`**.

**Example (when QA automation is in scope):** If **`prd-locked`** or **`qa-analysis`** is missing, **do not** ask about **semantic automation or CSV waiver** first — follow the dependency chain in the active skill (e.g. **`commands/qa-write.md`**).

**Headline = immediate next step (not downstream machine eval):** When **`manual-test-cases.csv`** or **`qa-prd-analysis`** is still the gap, the **first heading / lead** in chat must be **that** artifact or skill — **not** **`## What unlocks machine eval`**, **`qa/semantic-automation.csv`**, or the full ordering table **as the primary section title**. **`docs/forge-one-step-horizon.md`** — **Headline = immediate next step**.
